<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<simulation id="EnzymeCatalysis" version="1" simulatorVersion="09" date="12/15/08">
    <name>&lt;b&gt;Enzyme Catalysis&lt;/b&gt;</name>
    <intro filename=""/>
    <debugger state="on"/> 
    <steps>
        <step id="create">
            <actions>
                <action event="create" name="theexplainer"  url="tools/text_explainer2.swf"  x="0" y="35" xscale="1"  yscale="1"/>
                <action event="create" name="thegrapher" url="tools/graphVariableAvgOverTimeMsg09.swf" x="350" y="375" xscale="1" yscale="1" /> 
                <action event="create" name="beaker" url="swfs/beakerplain.swf"  x="350" y="5" xscale="2"  yscale="1.5"/> 
                <action event="create" name="box1" url="tools/ligandBox09.swf"  x="358" y="31" xscale=".8"  yscale=".8"/>
                <action event="create" name="StoPCast" url="swfs/ActivationcastKey.swf"  x="350" y="335" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="create" name="StoPequation" url="swfs/Activationequation.swf"  x="340" y="365" xscale="1" yscale="1" />
                <action event="settimer" timer='12' advance='yes' resettimer='0' /><!--pause briefly to let the objects load, then continue-->
                
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title> </title>
                    <text>&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Simulation of Enzyme Catalysis with a Beaker"
                    </text>                  
                </object>
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="next" state="0"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Uncatalyzed Reaction">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="initialize" name="opener" />
                <action event="create" name="Energydiagram1" url="swfs/ActivationEnergy.swf"  x="520" y="300" xscale=".9" yscale=".9" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Uncatalyzed Reaction </title>
                    <text>In order to understand why enzyme catalyzed reactions are important we need to understand the difference in the energy diagrams that exists between a uncatalyzed and catalyzed reaction.
                        
In the simulation to the right you see the uncatalyzed reaction in which S is the substrate and P is the product.
                        
Press "Continue" to see the simulation run.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="StoPequation" state="hilight" action="1" />
                <object name="StoPCast" state="visible" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Continue" action="continue" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
        <step id="Uncatalyzed Simulation">
            <actions>
                <action event="record light"/>
                <action event="initialize" name="box1" params="leftBorder=10,rightBorder=390,topBorder=10,bottomBorder=200,leftBorder2=10,rightBorder2=390,topBorder2=10,bottomBorder2=200">
                    <molecules>                         <molecule numMolecules= "0" myID="0"/>     <!--This is a fudge if only one molecule seems to need to be here-->
                        <molecule numMolecules= "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "ligandblue"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5"  mytype="molecule"  myID="1"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" seperateinto="productidl?3,productidm?2,productidp?4,Kd?50,k?1000,Kcat?.03"/>           
                        <molecule numMolecules= "1"  numbound= "0" velocity= "40"  cast= "enzymeinv" angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30" x="200" y="200" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5"  mytype="molecule"  myID="2"  polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" />                                   
                        <molecule numMolecules= "50"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "ligandblue"   angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="50" y="50" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5" mytype="ligand"  myID="3"   polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" bindswith="molecule2.pocket1.bound,Kd?25,k?500,productidm?1"/>
                        <molecule numMolecules=  "0"  numbound= "0" velocity= "60"  cast= "product"  angle1= "45" angle2= "315" rotationVelocity="5"  rotation="30"   x="100" y="100" Xoffset="5" Yoffset="5" mytype="ligand"  myID="4"    polarity = "0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0" mybounce="true" isproduct="1" />     <!--isproduct="1"-->
                    </molecules>
                </action>
                <action event="initialize" name="opener" />
            </actions>
            <objects tutor="">
                <object name="beaker" state="visible"/>
                <object name="theexplainer" state="visible">
                    <title>Uncatalyzed Simulation</title>
                    <text>As you can see in the simulation very little product is created. This is primarily due to the large activation energy. 
                        
From the energy diagram you should realize that the probability of a S spontaneously having enough energy to move toward products is very very small evan though P is energetically favored .
                        
Click "Next" to see how this changes with an enzyme present.
                    </text>                  
                </object>
                <object name="Energydiagram1" state="visible" />
                <object name="box1" state="visible" />
                <object name="StoPCast" state="visible" />
                <object name="StoPequation" state="hilight" action="1" />
            </objects>
            <nextbutton text="Next" state="1"/>
            <prevbutton text="Back" state="0"/>
        </step>
    </steps>
</simulation>
